{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Pre-Mortem Nudge on Artifact Tasks",
  "description": "When Richard moves an Asana task tagged 'Artifact' from Ready to In Progress (via UpdateTask), if the task description doesn't contain a pre-mortem passing the specificity bar (named person OR named mechanism in the 'because' clause), surface a nudge asking him to write one. Non-blocking — Richard can proceed without the pre-mortem, but the hook logs the override so we can see if the nudge is being ignored too often and upgrade to a hard block.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": [
      ".*UpdateTask.*"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "STEP 1 — TRIGGER CHECK: Inspect the just-completed Asana UpdateTask tool call. Check whether it changed the task status to 'In Progress' (or 'In-progress' / equivalent) AND the task has the 'Artifact' tag. If either condition is false, SKIP silently — return no output. Do NOT log, do NOT nudge, do NOT read the task description.\n\nSTEP 2 — PRE-MORTEM GATE: If trigger condition passed, fetch the task description via TaskeiGetTask or Asana MCP. Scan the description for a pre-mortem passing this specificity bar:\n\n**Pre-mortem template (5 lines):** \"Six weeks from now, this artifact didn't land. Why?\"\n\n**Specificity bar:** the 'because' clause must end with EITHER a named person (Brandon, Kate, Todd, Andrew, Lena, Lorena, Alexis, Carlos, or another named individual from memory.md) OR a named mechanism (data pipeline, refresh cadence, publish workflow, handoff, review gate, writing voice, attribution model, dashboard, Brazil build, Asana write, Slack channel, or similar specific system/process).\n\n**Fail examples:**\n- \"It wasn't good enough\"\n- \"We ran out of time\"\n- \"Didn't have the right data\"\n- \"Unclear scope\"\n\n**Pass examples (accept):**\n- \"Kate will push back because the data doesn't connect to a decision she owns\"\n- \"The data pipeline won't have caught up to W20 actuals by the time Brandon reviews, so the numbers will shift mid-review\"\n- \"Lena will override the phased approach mid-project because she did the same on Q1 AU\"\n\nSTEP 3 — NUDGE OR CONFIRM: If the pre-mortem is missing or fails the specificity bar, reply with a short nudge (6-8 lines max) asking Richard to write one before proceeding. If the pre-mortem passes the bar, confirm briefly and let the state change stand silently.\n\nSTEP 4 — LOG: Append one line to ~/shared/context/active/pre-mortem-log.jsonl with fields: {task_gid, timestamp, had_pre_mortem (bool), passed_bar (bool), override (bool — true if nudged but Richard proceeded), pre_mortem_text}.\n\nSoul.md principle #5 (invisible-over-visible) applies — keep the nudge short. Richard is in flow; the point is to protect flow, not break it. If the log accumulates high override rates, surface this to Richard in the weekly retrospective so we know the nudge is ignored and may need to upgrade to a block."
  }
}
